code Procfile
```
Hit **Enter** — blank file opens in editor ✅

---

### Step 2 — In that opened file paste ONLY this one line:
```
web: gunicorn wsgi:app
```

---

### Step 3 — Press Ctrl+S to save

---

## ⚠️ Very Important!

When VS Code asks to save — make sure filename is exactly:
```
Procfile
```
NOT:
```
Procfile.txt  ❌
procfile      ❌
PROCFILE      ❌
```

**Exactly** `Procfile` with capital P! ✅

---

## ✅ Your Folder Should Now Look Like This:
```
E:\CyberShield\
├── app.py
├── wsgi.py
├── Procfile
├── requirements.txt
└── templates\
    └── index.html